The paper focuses on the security of smart buildings, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of IT and wireless technologies in smart buildings, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the lack of consideration of non-technical aspects, such as social and organizational factors, which could fall under cyberpsychology (cs.CY) and social informatics (cs.SI).
